"""
9_Local_Metrics.py — Zero-Cost Automated Evaluation
=====================================================

Two automated evaluation methods that use NO LLM API calls at all beyond
generating the answers themselves (which the experiment needs regardless).
This makes them immune to Gemini's daily quota — they can be re-run
as many times as needed, any time of day.

1. SEMANTIC ANSWER SIMILARITY
   Cosine similarity between each generated answer and a short reference
   answer, computed with the same local sentence-transformers model
   already used for retrieval. For out-of-scope questions, the reference
   answer is the ideal refusal text — so this also rewards a system for
   correctly declining to answer, and penalises hallucination.

2. RETRIEVAL PRECISION / RECALL / MRR
   Classic information-retrieval metrics. For each in-scope question, you
   record which page(s) of the source document actually contain the
   answer. The system then checks whether the chunks FAISS retrieved
   actually came from those pages — entirely computed from rag.search()
   output, no model involved at all beyond the embedding lookup itself.

Both require you to fill in ground truth ONCE (reference answers + page
numbers) — saved to the database so you never need to re-enter it.
"""

